1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:03,900
You're reading a magazine. You come
across a full-page nude photo of a girl.

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:07,340
Is this testing whether I'm a
replicant or a lesbian, Mr. Deckard?

3
00:00:07,420 --> 00:00:08,780
Just answer the questions, please.

4
00:00:14,140 --> 00:00:18,420
You show it to your husband. He likes it
so much he hangs it on your bedroom wall.

5
00:00:20,315 --> 00:00:21,315
I wouldn't let him.

6
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,400
Why not?

7
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:26,051
I should be in there for him.

8
00:00:30,950 --> 00:00:31,950
One more question.

9
00:00:33,620 --> 00:00:36,240
You're watching a stage play.
A banquet is in progress.

10
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:39,520
The guests are enjoying
an appetizer of raw oysters.

11
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:43,060
The entree consists of boiled dog.

12
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,440
Would you step out for
a few moments, Rachel?

13
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:13,560
Thank you.

14
00:01:16,261 --> 00:01:18,440
She's a replicant, isn't she?

15
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,480
I'm impressed.

16
00:01:20,260 --> 00:01:23,160
How many questions does
it usually take to spot one?

17
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:24,440
I don't get it, Tyrell.

18
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:25,860
How many questions?

19
00:01:26,240 --> 00:01:27,700
Twenty, thirty, cross-referenced.

20
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,540
It took more than a
hundred for Rachel, didn't it?

21
00:01:31,580 --> 00:01:32,580
She doesn't know.

22
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,540
She's beginning to suspect, I think.

23
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:37,820
Suspect? How can it not know what it is?

24
00:01:38,420 --> 00:01:41,180
Commerce is our goal here at Tyrell.

25
00:01:41,181 --> 00:01:42,880
More human than human is our motto.

26
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,960
Rachel is an experiment.

27
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,500
Nothing more.

28
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:52,180
We began to recognize in
them a strange obsession.

29
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:55,497
After all, they are emotionally
inexperienced with only a few years

30
00:01:55,509 --> 00:01:58,800
in which to store up the experiences
which you and I take for granted.

31
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:04,597
If we gift them for the past,
we create a cushion or pillow

32
00:02:04,709 --> 00:02:07,940
for their emotions and consequently
we can control them better.

33
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:09,040
Memories.

34
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:11,520
You're talking about memories.

